    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FIXED MITER GEARS</title>
        <para>Steering gears using the fixed location miter gear arrangement have a non-adjustable relief plunger in the
            miter end of the steering gear. Proper relief adjustment can be made by lengthening or shortening the drag
            link. Relief plunger adjustment for the opposite end of the steering gear is made by adjusting the relief
            plunger as detailed in the foregoing paragraphs (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f05004d6">Figure 136</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f05004d6" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g05004d6" filename="../figg05/G05004d6.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 136. Adjust Relief Plunger</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
